author: Matthew Cahill
title: Tuesday's roundup | Bayside spikes Ocean Lakes
text:
BOYS VOLLEYBALL Bayside 3, Ocean Lakes 1
Luke Martin tallied 17 kills, Sean Davidson had 43 assists and the No. 3 Marlins knocked off the No. 1 Dolphins on Tuesday to claim sole possession of first place in the Coastal Conference.
Davidson added six aces for the Marlins (11-5, 7-1). Triniti Gadsden had 11 kills and Mike King had nine blocks.
The teams traded the first two sets with Bayside winning the first 25-18 and Ocean Lakes rebounding with a 25-20 win. But the Marlins closed it out with 25-22 and 25-18 wins in the third and fourth sets, respectively.
____
Green Run 3, Salem 2
Na'Jon Nobles delivered 34 assists, Torey Fields had 14 kills and the Stallions edged the SunDevils 25-13, 25-18, 15-25, 22-25, 16-14.
____
Cox 3, Landstown 0
Brad Creamer paced the No. 2 Falcons with 14 kills and Grant Gilden added 22 assists in the 25-19, 25-12, 25-23 Coastal Conference victory.
____
Great Bridge 3, Churchland 0
Perry Dunkum posted a team-high 14 kills, Christian Kangas had seven aces and the No. 8 Wildcats swept the Truckers 25-12, 25-14, 25-20.
Jackson Parker and Jason Jones had 14 assists apiece for Great Bridge.
___
GIRLS VOLLEYBALL
Nansemond-Suffolk 3,
Peninsula Catholic 1
Nicole Wright supplied 43 assists and the No. 5 Saints (19-7, 4-0) beat the Knights 30-28, 25-17, 16-25, 25-19.
The Saints' Livi Bono and Lindsay Knierbein had 18 kills apiece, while Logan Harrell had 31 digs.
____
FIELD HOCKEY
Cape Henry 1, Walsingham 0
Alexandra Land scored with two minutes remaining in the first half on Virginia Apperson's assist, and the Dolphins blanked the Trojans in a Tidewater Conference match-up.
____
First Colonial 4, Ocean Lakes 1
Reagan Bonniwell paced the second-ranked Patriots with two goals in a Coastal Conference win over the Dolphins.
____
Bishop Sullivan 4, Norfolk Collegiate 0
Mary Mooney netted a pair of goals as the Crusaders blanked the Oaks.
____
BOYS SOCCER
Cape Henry 4, Walsingham 0
Carson Averette and Conor Somers scored two goals apiece as the Dolphins (7-4-3) blanked the Trojans.
____
Nansemond-Suffolk 4,
Peninsula Catholic 2
Tanner Jackson recorded a hat trick to lead the Saints to their first Tidewater Conference win.
____
CROSS COUNTRY
Conference 17 meet
Dayton Pack and Carley Hill led the Great Bridge boys and girls teams to victories in the conference's first meet.
Pack finished the Bells Mill Park course in 17 minutes, 15 seconds. Lake Taylor's Courtney Fullilove and Great Bridge's Brogan McGlynn were second and third, respectively.
Hill completed the course in 19:49.24, nearly two minutes ahead of second-place Tamera Washington of Churchland.
